\f1\b\fs36\li1400 Class Description\b0\f0\fs16\
\
\f0\fs28\li2200 Message instances are used for forwarding Objective-C messages.  When an object doesn't respond to a message, the {\f2 doesNotUnderstand:} method is invoked, with an argument that is an instance of this class :\fs16\
\
\f2\fs24\li2800 - doesNotUnderstand:msg\
  \{\
    [msg sentTo:someObject];\
    return self;\
  \}\
\
\f0\fs16\
\f0\fs28\li2200 The user may override {\f2 -doesNotUnderstand:} to send a {\f2 sentTo:} message, which will forward the message to {\i someObject}.  If {\i someObject} doesn't respond to the message, it will receive a {\f2 doesNotUnderstand:} message, and so on.\fs16\
\
\f0\fs28\li2200 {\b {\f1 Note:}} To forward class (factory) methods, override the class method {\f2 +doesNotUnderstand:}.\fs16\
\
\f0\fs28\li2200 Also see Object's {\f2 doesNotUnderstand:} method for more details.\fs16\
